 @yusufismail91  Ini oke banget ditanyakan, saya jadi berpikir lagi perannya di semua ini wkwkw. Saya malah merasa dia jadi penghubung aja. Menghubungkan masa lalu (cerita para "perampok gunung", menyimpan peralatan mereka, dll) dan masa kini (jadi update info ke pak Kim, menyediakan makan malam dan nourishment buat tim mereka). 

Tapi sepertinya dia out of touch dengan Feng Shui. Awal2 kenalan, Pak Kim sempet bilang dia kenalin simbol Fengshui di temple itu. Tp kayaknya si bapak2 penjaga kuil out of touch, ga kenalin atau align dengan ahli Fengshui yang malah dicap "perampok". Pasak bertuliskan nama dan buku2 Feng Shui nya malah dibiarkan di gudang, ga dipelajarin. Akibatnya dia jadi korban si Shogun tsb, diambil liver nya. 

Menariknya liver dalam bahasa Jepang Kimo. Kalau jurit malam dalam bahasa Jepangnya Kimodameshi. Liver itu memang dianggep jadi perwakilan keberanian seseorang di sana.

 @ttttola02  in terms of jump scares the movie doesn't have more than around 3,it focuses on story telling instead,I wouldn't go as far as to say that the movie was really scary rather it was a nice thriller movie with an insane plot twist at the end,

Anyway it's probably a 5/10 on the jump scares scale

But don't let that stop you from seeing the movie because it gets SO GOOD after the first hour

 @mumumaxima  I've been into korean culture since 2011, and I have always been a huge movie addict, especially western movies. I never lose my judgement and I know when something is good, doesn't matter where it's from. I've watched a lot A LOT of movies, specifically horror/thriller from both US and S Korea, and this movie got me stunted almost the whole time in the cinema. The whole production is just perfect, including the actors. 
And bcs I was already familiar with the shamanism there in SK, and as an Asian myself it's just natural for us to have those kind of cultural believes.

